05:39.556 --> 05:41.253
Sarah, good to see you.

05:42.211 --> 05:43.865
You are right on time.

05:45.867 --> 05:47.564
Let's grab a seat and get comfy.

05:49.479 --> 05:51.002
So, did your mom drop you off?

05:51.089 --> 05:52.700
- Yeah, she said she
would come get me later.

05:52.787 --> 05:54.092
- Okay, good.

05:54.179 --> 05:55.485
Oh, I saw you
brought your journal.

05:55.572 --> 05:57.269
- Mm-hmm.
- Great, thank you.

05:59.054 --> 06:01.099
I give you almost as much
work as your teacher, eh?

06:01.186 --> 06:03.624
[laughing]

06:03.711 --> 06:04.451
Good.

06:05.843 --> 06:06.409
Good.

06:08.106 --> 06:10.457
So, tell me, what's been
going on in your life lately?

06:10.544 --> 06:12.633
- I mean, just problems at home,

06:12.720 --> 06:14.374
my parents are always fighting

06:14.461 --> 06:16.637
and it's just hard for me.

06:16.724 --> 06:20.205
- So, Skyler, you are
looking beautiful.

06:20.292 --> 06:21.555
Things are going well.

06:22.730 --> 06:24.427
[knocking]

06:24.514 --> 06:26.647
Roxanne, hey.

06:26.734 --> 06:27.996
What are you doing?

06:28.083 --> 06:29.693
No, no, go around.

06:29.780 --> 06:31.869
I told you before, use the door.

06:32.957 --> 06:34.350
Geez.

06:34.437 --> 06:35.743
[bright music]

06:35.830 --> 06:37.701
Roxanne, that's
what doors are for.

06:37.788 --> 06:38.876
- Who uses doors?

06:38.963 --> 06:39.790
- [Alex] Normal people.

06:39.877 --> 06:41.270
- Boring people.

06:41.357 --> 06:44.012
Hey, all right, so I
am breaking you out

06:44.099 --> 06:45.579
of this office for lunch.

06:45.666 --> 06:47.102
- Okay.

06:47.189 --> 06:48.843
- I was thinking out
favorite Italian restaurant,

06:48.930 --> 06:51.193
the one with the really
great mozzarella,

06:51.280 --> 06:53.804
and the cute owner's son
who has the hots for you.

06:55.240 --> 06:57.417
- No, he does not.
- Yes, he does.

06:57.504 --> 06:58.635
You don't think I notice?

06:58.722 --> 07:00.028
