ridicule and harass me.

01:07:29.915 --> 01:07:31.351
I know your end game.

01:07:31.438 --> 01:07:34.224
- Well, I mean you are
kinda funny looking,

01:07:34.311 --> 01:07:35.790
so you make me look good.

01:07:36.878 --> 01:07:38.228
- Don't be hatin' on all this.

01:07:38.315 --> 01:07:40.665
[Alex laughs]

01:07:42.014 --> 01:07:44.712
- No, honestly, Max...

01:07:47.454 --> 01:07:50.979
The kids do really like you
and you're great with them,

01:07:51.067 --> 01:07:54.157
and I guess I kinda like
having you around, too.

01:07:56.159 --> 01:07:58.726
- Of course you do,
I'm Max Rothschild.

01:08:01.381 --> 01:08:03.470
- Hey, will you excuse
me for a minute.

01:08:04.863 --> 01:08:06.299
I think I'd better
go talk to CJ.

01:08:06.386 --> 01:08:07.126
- Okay.

01:08:16.657 --> 01:08:18.136
- Hey, CJ.

01:08:18.224 --> 01:08:19.006
How you doing?

01:08:20.921 --> 01:08:22.533
You wanna go in for a swim?

01:08:26.885 --> 01:08:27.625
Why not?

01:08:28.712 --> 01:08:30.453
- I don't wanna get sunburned.

01:08:31.933 --> 01:08:33.935
- Is that the real reason?

01:08:34.022 --> 01:08:34.805
Hey.

01:08:44.032 --> 01:08:47.122
Did I ever tell you
about when I was 15?

01:08:48.689 --> 01:08:51.692
I went through a hard
time, abusive relationship.

01:08:55.392 --> 01:08:56.479
At one point the pain got so bad

01:08:58.220 --> 01:09:02.094
I felt like if I couldn't get
it out I wouldn't survive.

01:09:02.180 --> 01:09:04.314
So, I started to.

01:09:06.707 --> 01:09:07.621
- To hurt yourself?

01:09:10.885 --> 01:09:12.496
But you're Ms. Alex.

01:09:13.584 --> 01:09:14.541
- I'm also human.

01:09:17.587 --> 01:09:20.068
- How did you know about...

01:09:21.026 --> 01:09:21.809
me?

01:09:24.247 --> 01:09:25.117
- I've been there.

01:09:29.381 --> 01:09:30.166
CJ...

01:09:33.473 --> 01:09:34.866
God's love brought me back.

01:09:37.260 --> 01:09:40.045
- I don't think God
loves me all that much.

01:09:40.131 --> 01:09:42.352
- No, no, CJ, God loves you.

01:09:43.657 --> 01:09:45.093
Why would you say that?

01:09:45.180 --> 01:09:47.051
- I did the whole
church thing, Ms. A.

01:09:50.881 --> 01:09:53.276
I know The Bible says
that God is my Father.

01:09:56.366 --> 01:09:58.281
What kind of father
lets their child suffer?

01:10:03.547 --> 01:10:07.115
It just feels like he's
turned his back on me.

01:10:10.118 --> 01:10:12.164
And I'm so tired of feeling...

01:10:15.515 --> 01:10:16.342
worthless.

01:10:18.997 --> 01:10:20.128
I just wanna...

01:10:21.129 --> 01:10:22.566
I wanna feel--

01:10:22.653 --> 01:10:23.349
- Whole again?

01:10:27.353 --> 01:10:30.835
CJ, his love, it's so faithful.

01:10:30.922 --> 01:10:32.967
He takes you just as you are,

01:10:33.054 --> 01:10:35.274
but he doesn't leave
you the way you are.

01:10:35.361 --> 01:10:36.841
His love is there
when you wake up,

01:10:36.928 --> 01:10:39.974
when you open your eyes,
when you take a breath,

01:10:40.061 --> 01:10:41.237
when your heart beats.

01:10:42.499 --> 01:10:43.587
Every minute of every day,

01:10:45.023 --> 01:10:46.372
he can love you
back to wholeness.

01:10:47.808 --> 01:10:50.115
- You really think so?
- I know so.

01:10:51.464 --> 01:10:53.336
I know he loves you.

01:10:53.423 --> 01:10:56.077
God is the one person
that will never,

01:10:56.164 --> 01:10:57.905
ever leave you or forsake you.

01:10:58.863 --> 01:11:00.299
He will never judge you.

01:11:03.302 --> 01:11:05.478
He will always love you.

01:11:07.088 --> 01:11:10.309
- I love you, Ms. A.
- I love you, too.

01:11:10.396 --> 01:11:11.528
Can I give you a hug?

01:11:13.138 --> 01:11:13.921
- Yeah.

01:11:18.535 --> 01:11:20.450
- You know what?

01:11:20.537 --> 01:11:22.452
All these kids here,
they love you, too.

01:11:24.192 --> 01:11:26.020
If you ever need
anyone to talk to,

01:11:26.107 --> 01:11:27.239
we're all here for you.

01:11:29.372 --> 01:11:32.810
- Hey, so we're about to
start the cannonball contest.

01:11:32.897 --> 01:11:33.854
Y'all wanna?

01:11:33.941 --> 01:11:35.203
- Hey, CJ and I could be judges.

01:11:35.291 --> 01:11:36.335
- Oh, that's great.

01:11:36.422 --> 01:11:38.032
Hey, kids, we're about to start

01:11:38.119 --> 01:11:39.338
the cannonball contest, come on!

01:11:40.513 --> 01:11:45.475
- Come on, C.
[exciting music]

01:12:15.766 --> 01:12:17.463
- I'm so sorry,
Mr. DelaHoussaye,

01:12:17.550 --> 01:12:19.813
they refused to stop at
the front desk and sign in.

01:12:19.900 --> 01:12:21.337
- It's okay, Stacy.

01:12:21.424 --> 01:12:23.339
I know these two fine,
upstanding gentlemen.

01:12:23.426 --> 01:12:24.383
I'm good.

01:12:24.470 --> 01:12:25.253
Thank you so much.

01:12:27.255 --> 01:12:31.782
- Chandler Hollywood
DelaHoussaye, in the flesh.

01:12:31.869 --> 01:12:33.740
- Howdy, boys, what
can I do for you?

01:12:33.827 --> 01:12:36.308
- Mr. Marcello would
like his money today.

01:12:38.441 --> 01:12:41.400
- I just spoke with
Mr. Marcello last week,

01:12:41.487 --> 01:12:42.880
we have an agreement.

01:12:42.967 --> 01:12:44.534
We have a special bond.

01:12:44.621 --> 01:12:46.187
Everything's gonna
be fine, guys.

01:12:47.406 --> 01:12:48.320
- I don't think pretty boy here

01:12:48.407 --> 01:12:51.149
is on the same page as the boss.

01:12:51.236 --> 01:12:53.064
Mind I should rattle
his cage a little?

01:12:53.151 --> 01:12:55.240
- Not just yet.

01:12:55.327 --> 01:12:58.112
Mr. Marcello likes
his money on time,

01:12:58.199 --> 01:12:59.853
and let me tell you
something, little man,

01:12:59.940 --> 01:13:01.507
if you love anything
about yourself,

01:13:01.594 --> 01:13:03.379
your business, or
whatever you do,

01:13:03.466 --> 01:13:05.206
you're gonna have
that money today.

01:13:05.293 --> 01:13:06.294
Do you understand me?

01:13:06.382 --> 01:13:08.166
Are you hearing me?

01:13:08.253 --> 01:13:09.254
- I hear you guys.

01:13:09.341 --> 01:13:11.256
Everything is crystal clear.

01:13:11.343 --> 01:13:12.431
- Let's hope so.

01:13:13.476 --> 01:13:15.695
[Alex sighs deeply]

01:13:15.782 --> 01:13:16.957
- This is a great idea.

01:13:20.700 --> 01:13:22.136
[sighs]

01:13:22.223 --> 01:13:23.529
Max...

01:13:23.616 --> 01:13:24.965
Do you really think the kids

01:13:25.052 --> 01:13:26.663
are gonna be ready
for tomorrow night?

01:13:26.750 --> 01:13:27.664
- Yeah, I think they're as ready

01:13:27.751 --> 01:13:29.448
as they're ever gonna be.

01:13:29.535 --> 01:13:30.928
- And you know, I looked online,

01:13:31.015 --> 01:13:33.496
there are 681
tickets sold already.

01:13:33.583 --> 01:13:35.193
- 681 tickets?

01:13:36.803 --> 01:13:39.066
That's more than I had at
my last show in New York.

01:13:40.633 --> 01:13:43.201
- Well, this endeavor
may not save the center,

01:13:43.288 --> 01:13:44.594
but at least I'll know

01:13:44.681 --> 01:13:45.638
we did everything
we possibly could.

01:13:47.466 --> 01:13:49.033
- Yeah.

01:13:49.120 --> 01:13:51.775
We really did get this together
pretty good, didn't we?

01:13:53.646 --> 01:13:55.431
You know, you and I
make a great team.

01:13:57.650 --> 01:14:00.218
- Well, I really
should thank you again.

01:14:02.133 --> 01:14:03.177
You didn't have
to come and rescue

01:14:03.264 --> 01:14:04.701
me and all my problems.

01:14:06.311 --> 01:14:08.400
- I kinda like being your
knight in shining armor.

01:14:10.533 --> 01:14:12.970
It's worth it to see that
beautiful smile again.

01:14:14.711 --> 01:14:16.626
- Oh sir, you make me blush.

01:14:21.108 --> 01:14:23.502
Seriously, would you like
to take walk on the pier?

01:14:24.590 --> 01:14:25.373
- I'd love to.

01:14:26.549 --> 01:14:29.247
[romantic music]

01:14:52.444 --> 01:14:55.795
[Alex and Max whispering]

01:15:33.790 --> 01:15:35.531
Hey, Roxy, have you seen Alex?

01:15:35.618 --> 01:15:36.662
- Yeah, she was here earlier

01:15:36.749 --> 01:15:38.229
but she went back to the center

01:15:38.316 --> 01:15:39.360
to get the kids' presents
for after the show.

01:15:39.447 --> 01:15:40.144
She'll be back soon.

01:15:40.231 --> 01:15:41.537
- Okay, thanks.

01:15:41.624 --> 01:15:43.016
- Max, Max, do you
have the batteries

01:15:43.103 --> 01:15:45.584
for the wireless mics?
- Yeah, batteries.

01:15:45.671 --> 01:15:49.066
Okay, A/V booth, under
the console on the shelf.

01:15:49.153 --> 01:15:49.980
I think they should be there.

01:15:50.067 --> 01:15:51.329
- Okay, I'll check 'em all,

01:15:51.416 --> 01:15:52.765
put the batteries
in and test 'em.

01:15:52.852 --> 01:15:54.767
- Hey, wait, wait,
wait, before you go,

01:15:54.854 --> 01:15:56.682
remember, we do need to label

01:15:56.769 --> 01:15:59.642
each one independently,
each channel.

01:15:59.729 --> 01:16:01.557
We can't have any mess
ups tonight, okay?

01:16:01.644 --> 01:16:03.559
- From your lips to God's ears.

01:16:03.646 --> 01:16:04.734
- Thanks, Roberto.

01:16:06.257 --> 01:16:07.388
[sighs] Where'd she go?

01:16:12.263 --> 01:16:14.482
[humming]

01:16:16.006 --> 01:16:18.138
- Good afternoon, Ms. Park.

01:16:18.225 --> 01:16:19.444
I've been waiting for you.

01:16:20.401 --> 01:16:21.446
- How did you get in here?

01:16:22.882 --> 01:16:25.450
- Door was unlocked,
I let myself in.

01:16:26.451 --> 01:16:29.323
- Well, you're trespassing.

01:16:29.410 --> 01:16:31.325
This is private property.

01:16:31.412 --> 01:16:33.153
I'd like you to leave now.

01:16:33.240 --> 01:16:34.981
- Not so quick, missy.

01:16:35.068 --> 01:16:37.114
We have some business
to conduct here.

01:16:37.201 --> 01:16:41.597
- Listen, Mr. Chandler, I don't
know who you think you are

01:16:41.684 --> 01:16:45.775
but I already told you, this
building is not for sale.

01:16:45.862 --> 01:16:47.037
Now, please leave.

01:16:47.124 --> 01:16:48.604
- Well, come Monday morning

01:16:48.691 --> 01:16:52.608
you will no longer own this
property, the bank will.

01:16:52.695 --> 01:16:55.611
I am merely here as
to assist your exit.

01:16:55.698 --> 01:16:56.699
Here.

01:16:59.136 --> 01:16:59.876
This is for you.

01:17:11.757 --> 01:17:13.933
[ripping]

01:17:16.327 --> 01:17:19.373
- Now get out before
I call the police.

01:17:19.460 --> 01:17:22.638
- That was not a wise move.

01:17:22.725 --> 01:17:23.726
- Get out!

01:17:25.945 --> 01:17:26.685
- After you.

01:17:37.914 --> 01:17:40.394
[bat clinking]

01:17:41.831 --> 01:17:43.920
You should've taken
the money, lady.

01:17:46.836 --> 01:17:49.708
[freezer whirring]

01:18:02.808 --> 01:18:05.593
It's a shame, such
a pretty woman.

01:18:06.899 --> 01:18:08.248
It didn't have to be this way,

01:18:09.772 --> 01:18:12.165
but I'm taking that teen
center back from you.

01:18:12.252 --> 01:18:13.863
You just sit in here and chill.

01:18:18.128 --> 01:18:20.521
- Roxy, did Alex
ever get back yet?

01:18:20.608 --> 01:18:21.871
- No.
- It's an hour till show time,

01:18:21.958 --> 01:18:23.568
I'm starting to get worried.

01:18:23.655 --> 01:18:25.744
- No, but maybe she stopped
at her apartment or something.

01:18:25.831 --> 01:18:26.876
Did you try calling her?

01:18:26.963 --> 01:18:28.355
- I did.

01:18:28.442 --> 01:18:30.140
It just keeps rolling
over to voicemail.

01:18:30.227 --> 01:18:31.750
- That's not like her.

01:18:31.837 --> 01:18:33.012
Maybe I should go look for her.

01:18:33.099 --> 01:18:34.797
- No, no, look, I got it, okay?

01:18:34.884 --> 01:18:36.842
Look, you and Roberto are
gonna be in charge, okay?

01:18:36.929 --> 01:18:38.844
- What?
- Not for the whole thing,

01:18:38.931 --> 01:18:40.324
just at least until
I get back, okay?

01:18:40.411 --> 01:18:41.238
You've got this, okay?

01:18:41.325 --> 01:18:42.805
You've got this.

01:18:42.892 --> 01:18:44.720
You're in charge, but I'll
be back as soon as I can.

01:18:47.157 --> 01:18:48.724
- I'm in charge now.

01:18:48.811 --> 01:18:53.729
[slow piano music]
[audience chattering]

01:19:11.834 --> 01:19:12.573
[knocking]

01:19:12.660 --> 01:19:13.749
- Alex.

01:19:13.836 --> 01:19:14.706
Alex.

01:19:14.793 --> 01:19:16.229
Alex, are you in there?

01:19:16.316 --> 01:19:18.405
You sure picked a heck
of a day to go MIA.

01:19:19.537 --> 01:19:21.452
[intense music]

01:19:21.539 --> 01:19:24.542
[breathing heavily]

01:19:31.897 --> 01:19:33.246
- You've gotta be kidding me.

01:19:36.162 --> 01:19:37.076
Hey!

01:19:37.163 --> 01:19:41.733
Hey!
[groaning]

01:19:41.820 --> 01:19:43.169
No!

01:19:43.256 --> 01:19:44.083
Let me out!

01:19:45.563 --> 01:19:48.566
[breathing heavily]

01:19:50.307 --> 01:19:52.613
[groaning]

01:20:18.814 --> 01:20:20.946
[shivering]

01:20:28.911 --> 01:20:29.912
Come on.

01:20:39.922 --> 01:20:40.661
Max.

01:20:42.228 --> 01:20:43.403
Hey, babe.

01:20:45.101 --> 01:20:47.059
I'm sure you're
wondering what happened.

01:20:48.582 --> 01:20:53.109
This guy named Chandler
DelaHoussaye, I think.

01:20:53.196 --> 01:20:56.547
He came by my office,
offered to buy me out.

01:20:57.940 --> 01:21:01.117
I turned him down,
guess he didn't like it.

01:21:02.901 --> 01:21:03.859
Next thing I knew...

01:21:06.122 --> 01:21:08.037
I woke up in the
center's freezer.

01:21:13.651 --> 01:21:16.219
[bells ringing]

01:21:18.395 --> 01:21:21.180
- Go, therefore, and make
disciples of all nations

01:21:21.267 --> 01:21:23.356
as I have made of you, Peter,

01:21:23.443 --> 01:21:25.968
baptizing them in the
name of the Father,

01:21:26.055 --> 01:21:29.058
and of the Son, and
of the Holy Spirit.

01:21:29.145 --> 01:21:32.104
- Yes, Rabbi.
[slow music]

01:21:36.935 --> 01:21:38.458
♪ The clock ticks ♪

01:21:38.545 --> 01:21:40.460
♪ And tocks ♪

01:21:40.547 --> 01:21:44.073
♪ The devil down in Hell mocks ♪

01:21:44.160 --> 01:21:47.119
♪ Our lives just fall apart ♪

01:21:47.206 --> 01:21:50.470
♪ It's so bad that
it hurts my heart ♪

01:21:50.557 --> 01:21:54.170
♪ What happened to morality ♪

01:21:54.257 --> 01:21:57.869
♪ Our parents teach us to see ♪

01:21:57.956 --> 01:22:00.611
♪ How much more can we take ♪

01:22:00.698 --> 01:22:05.616
♪ Before humanity just breaks ♪

01:22:09.750 --> 01:22:14.190
♪ God needs some heroes ♪

01:22:14.277 --> 01:22:16.757
♪ To appear ♪

01:22:16.844 --> 01:22:21.110
♪ God needs some heroes ♪

01:22:21.197 --> 01:22:23.460
♪ To appear ♪

01:22:23.547 --> 01:22:26.942
♪ Fight all the bad guys ♪

01:22:27.029 --> 01:22:30.206
♪ Make right all the bad times ♪

01:22:30.293 --> 01:22:34.862
♪ God needs some heroes ♪

01:22:34.950 --> 01:22:37.126
♪ To appear ♪

01:22:37.213 --> 01:22:42.174
♪ I'll have no fear ♪

01:22:44.176 --> 01:22:49.094
♪ I'll have no fear ♪

01:22:49.965 --> 01:22:51.705
♪ Oh, oh ♪

01:23:10.420 --> 01:23:13.510
- [sighs] Voicemail.

01:23:15.338 --> 01:23:17.514
Hang on, Alex, I'm coming.

01:23:18.645 --> 01:23:21.126
[bright music]

01:24:07.825 --> 01:24:08.521
- Max...

01:24:08.608 --> 01:24:10.828
[shivers]

01:24:12.438 --> 01:24:13.178
I'm sorry.

01:24:15.137 --> 01:24:16.573
Tell the kids I'm sorry.

01:24:20.272 --> 01:24:21.273
Please...

01:24:24.146 --> 01:24:27.236
Tell them I'd never leave them.

01:24:27.323 --> 01:24:29.412
I'd never leave them
if I had a choice.

01:24:37.159 --> 01:24:38.856
Please take care of my kids.

01:24:41.206 --> 01:24:43.121
Don't let the center
shut down, Max.

01:25:17.286 --> 01:25:19.723
And you know, I never told you,

01:25:19.810 --> 01:25:21.812
and I should've told
you a long time ago,

01:25:24.249 --> 01:25:25.032
I love you.

01:25:27.252 --> 01:25:29.080
I don't just like
having you around...

01:25:32.388 --> 01:25:33.171
I need you around.

01:25:36.696 --> 01:25:38.176
I never should've let you go,

01:25:39.612 --> 01:25:41.266
and I'm sorry I pushed you away.

01:25:44.748 --> 01:25:45.792
I was scared.

01:25:49.361 --> 01:25:50.145
I was scared.

01:25:51.668 --> 01:25:52.930
I was an idiot.

01:25:56.803 --> 01:25:58.979
I didn't think that
you'd ever understand.

01:26:02.374 --> 01:26:05.334
[breathing heavily]

01:26:28.966 --> 01:26:32.143
♪ Amazing grace ♪

01:26:32.230 --> 01:26:36.669
♪ How sweet the sound ♪

01:26:36.756 --> 01:26:40.107
♪ When we've been there ♪

01:26:40.195 --> 01:26:43.546
♪ 10,000 years ♪

01:26:43.633 --> 01:26:47.071
♪ Bright shining as ♪

01:26:47.158 --> 01:26:49.465
♪ The sun ♪

01:26:49.552 --> 01:26:52.555
♪ We've no less days ♪

01:26:52.642 --> 01:26:55.906
♪ To sing God's praise ♪

01:26:55.993 --> 01:26:59.605
♪ Than when we'd first begun ♪

01:27:03.566 --> 01:27:05.742
[humming]

01:28:00.927 --> 01:28:03.669
- You know the time
is among us, mother,

01:28:03.756 --> 01:28:05.192
time for my father's prophecy

01:28:05.280 --> 01:28:06.498
to be fulfilled
as it was written.

01:28:06.585 --> 01:28:08.544
I know, my beloved son.

01:28:08.631 --> 01:28:12.156
You have given my life grace
and meaning for 33 years.

01:28:13.636 --> 01:28:15.812
What is the Lord's
purpose for me now?

01:28:15.899 --> 01:28:17.248
- To be the echo of my word

01:28:17.335 --> 01:28:19.294
to all you encounter.

01:28:19.381 --> 01:28:21.296
Use your faith and strength

01:28:21.383 --> 01:28:22.906
and shepherd in
what must be done

01:28:22.993 --> 01:28:24.777
for all humanity to survive.

01:28:25.865 --> 01:28:27.345
I know you have it in you.

01:28:27.432 --> 01:28:29.391
- I know, but my heart's desire

01:28:29.478 --> 01:28:31.436
has always been on you, my son.

01:28:33.569 --> 01:28:35.440
What will Heaven be like?

01:28:35.527 --> 01:28:37.660
